  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the apostles and elders came together,.... And also the brethren, or private members of the church, even the whole church, as appears from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 15:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Whether all the apostles were here present, is not certain; Peter, James, and John were; but who else, cannot be said: these met together ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for to consider of this matter; to hear what was to be said on both sides of the question, and then to judge what advice was proper to be given to the Gentiles. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "for to consider of this matter; to hear what was to be said on both sides of the question, and then to judge what advice was proper to be given to the Gentiles. ",
