      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 15:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") write of themselves: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἔδοξεν ἡμῖν γενομένοις ὁμοθυμαδόν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Against this it has been objected that no place would have sufficed to hold them, and therefore it is maintained that only ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "deputies of the church",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " took part (Mosheim, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "de reb. Christ. ante Const. M.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " p. 117, Kuinoel, Neander); but this is entirely arbitrary, as the text indicates nothing of such a limitation, and the locality is entirely unknown to us.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
